column2: COVID-19 response - % of orders since the outbreak of COVID-19 where partial or complete order cancellations applied
column3: COVID-19 response - % of orders since the outbreak of COVID-19 that have been cancelled and not been reinstated and paid in full
column4: COVID-19 response - % of orders since the outbreak of COVID-19 for which discounts on the previously agreed payment terms have been renegotiated
column5: COVID-19 response - % of workers that received late wage payments due to COVID-19
column6: COVID-19 response - % or number of workers in the brand’s supply chain that have been laid off as a result of COVID-19 (approximate % is sufficient)
column7: COVID-19 response - % that the brand’s Free On Board (FOB) prices have increased or decreased on average in the past 12 months
column8: Living wages - Discloses the company's approach to achieving the payment of living wages to workers in the supply chain
column9: Living wages - Publishes time-bound, measurable roadmap/strategy for how it will achieve a living wage for all workers across its supply chain
column10: Living wages - Reports on annual, measurable progress towards paying living wages to workers in the supply chain
column11: Living wages - Discloses what living wage estimates brand uses to track and benchmark wages for workers in its supply chain
column12: Living wages - % of workers that are receiving wage payments digitally
column13: Living wages - % above the minimum wage workers are paid in the brand’s supply chain
column14: Living wages - Discloses % or number of workers in supply chain that are being paid a living wage rate
column15: Purchasing practices - Discloses method for calculating and ring-fencing labour costs (including a wage rates + overtime, social security, sick leave, vacation and other forms of leave as well as the cost of indirect labour and wage increases) in price negotiations
column16: Purchasing practices - % of orders/volume for which wages and other labour costs (such as wages increases) are isolated/ring-fenced
column17: Purchasing practices - Publishes a standard supplier agreement template, setting out typical order and payment terms and conditions
column18: Purchasing practices - Discloses policy on what % of the purchase order the brand typically pays to the supplier up front before production begins (in order to cover things such as the cost of raw materials)
column19: Purchasing practices - Discloses policy to pay suppliers within a maximum of 60 days (e.g. via UK Prompt Payment Code commitments)
column20: Purchasing practices - Discloses the average number of days in which purchase orders are paid in full to suppliers after delivery
column21: Purchasing practices - % of retrospective changes made to orders or payment terms after the original purchase order agreement was made
column22: Purchasing practices - Discloses annual supplier feedback on the brands’ purchasing practices through a formal process (e.g. via Better Buying platform, Supplier Summits, internal surveys of suppliers of brands’ purchasing practices)
column23: Unionisation & collective bargaining - Number or % of supplier facilities that have independent, democratically elected trade unions
column24: Unionisation & collective bargaining - Number or % of workers in the supply chain that are covered by collective bargaining agreements
column25: Unionisation & collective bargaining - Number of collective bargaining agreements that provide wages that are higher than required by local law for workers in the supply chain
column26: Unionisation & collective bargaining - Publishes data on the prevalence of collective bargaining and freedom of association related violations in supplier facilities
